    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "020a026c47f24536",
      "text": "Banco Palmas is a community bank in Fortaleza, Brazil. Since 2000, it has offered interest-free microcredit loans in the local currency, the Palmas. The bank’s objective is to localise production and consumption and, through the Palmas, retain more wealth within the area, generating both employment and income. Banco Palmas illustrates the benefits of a strong local banking sector for local economies, acting as a trusted backer of the community currency.\nThe example has now spread to over 100 locations across Brazil, and is acknowledged by the central bank as a valuable initiative."
    },
